Figure 9diagram AddressFeature {
  title 'Address feature'
  caption 'Address feature data model'
  class AddressFeature {
    definition {
  Address feature represents the status of a particular aspect of an
interchange address instance, as determined by an address processor.
Each of the aspects may be differentiated by multiple statuses.

This is an abstract class.
To represent specific features, this class should be extended upon.

}
    +signature: Signature [0..1]{
  definition {
  Cryptographic signature used to ensure that the
feature is marked by an address process trusted for
verification of this feature.
The signature generated shall incorporate the `id` attribute
of the interchange address instance that owns it.
}
}
  }
  class SpecificationLevel {
    definition {
  When an address is first manually entered by a common person, it is
unrealistic to expect this person to fully adhere to the defined
structure.

The allowed values of specification levels are:

* Fully structured, all components are accurately separated and cannot
be further split.

* Partially structured, some components may be structurally
correct, but some other components are still unstructured.

* Unstructured, the user has entered free-form text with no regard of
structuring them.

[example]
Digital addresses entered on e-commerce sites and address books
are often partially structured, with defined country, region
and city, but with street addresses often unstructured.

[example]
Digital addresses for utility installations
(e.g. electricity, water supplies) are often fully structured.

Therefore, an organization who accepts these addresses may wish to
re-structure them or fill in any missing address components.

}
    +value: SpecificationLevelValue {
  definition {
  Indicating the extent of specification of an address instance on its structure.
  }
}
  }
  association {
    owner SpecificationLevel
    member_type inheritance
    member AddressFeature
  }
  class QualityStatus {
    definition {
  An address entered may not have been validated for correctness.
An address processor, such as a postal handling entity,
may decide to validate the address to a certain degree
in order to determine the correctness of the address.

}
    +value: QualityCode {
  definition {
  Indicating the quality of an address instance.
  }
}
  }
  association {
    owner QualityStatus
    member_type inheritance
    member AddressFeature
  }
  class Geolocation {
    definition {
  An address is commonly linked to one or more geolocations.
The value of a location is given by `EX_Extent` defined
in <<ISO19115-1,clause=6.6.1>>, which supports
geographic, temporal and vertical specification.

}
    +value: iso19115EX_Extent {
  definition {
  The geographic, temporal and vertical information of the location defined in <<ISO19115-1,clause=6.6.1>>.
  }
}
  }
  association {
    owner Geolocation
    member_type inheritance
    member AddressFeature
  }
  enum SpecificationLevelValue {
    unstructured{
  definition {
  The user has entered free-form text with no regard of structuring them.
  }
}
    partial{
  definition {
  Some components may be structurally correct, but some other components are still unstructured.
  }
}
    full{
  definition {
  All components are accurately separated and cannot be further split.
  }
}
  }
  enum QualityCode {
    confirmedCorrect{
  definition {
  Indicating that the address is confirmed to be correct to the best of knowledge of the address processor.
  }
}
    mostlyCorrect{
  definition {
  Indicating with high confidence that the address is correct.
  }
}
    possiblyCorrect{
  definition {
  Indicating with confidence that the address is correct.
  }
}
    structurallyCorrect{
  definition {
  Indicating that the address components have the correct value types.
  }
}
    unknown{
  definition {
  Indicating that this address has not been validated in any way, and it cannot be assigned a quality.
  }
}
  }
}

Figure 10diagram LayoutTemplate {
  title 'Layout template'
  caption 'Layout template data model'
  class LayoutTemplate {
    definition {
  The interchange layout template serves as the basis of the
interchange display template and
the interchange form template.

A layout template is designed to present an
interchange address instance in the case of a display template, or
present an input form for entry of an interchange address instance
in the case of an interchange form template.

The interchange layout template is based on the following assumptions:

* the resulting layout is displayed in a bounded rectangular area

* the entire template is in the same script and locale.

The action of inserting components from a given interchange
address instance into a layout template is called "render".

// TODO: define "render" in terms and definition

[example]
A postal mail label can be conceptually considered as an
interchange address instance rendered according to a layout template.

}
    +id: CharacterString {
  definition {
  Unique identifier for the layout template.
  }
}
    +name: CharacterString {
  definition {
  Descriptive name of the layout template.
  }
}
    +description: CharacterString {
  definition {
  Textual description of the layout template.
  }
}
    +localization: Localization {
  definition {
  Locale and script information of the layout template.
  }
}
    +dimension: LayoutDimension [0..*]{
  definition {
  Physical dimensions of the rectangular bounding box for the rendered layout output.
  }
}
    +orientation: LayoutOrientation [0..1]{
  definition {
  Horizontal or vertical of the text orientation.
  }
}
    +lines: LayoutLine [0..*]{
  definition {
  The constituent parts of this LayoutTemplate.
  }
}
  }
  class LayoutDimension {
    definition {
  Physical dimensions of the rectangular bounding box for the rendered layout output.

}
    +width: Integer [0..1]{
  definition {
  The horizontal length of the rectangular bounding box for the rendered layout output.
  }
}
    +height: Integer [0..1]{
  definition {
  The vertical length of the rectangular bounding box for the rendered layout output.
  }
}
  }
  enum LayoutOrientation {
    definition {
  The enumeration value to indicate the orientation of the address rendered by the LayoutTemplate.
}
    horizontal{
  definition {
  Indicating that the address will be rendered from left to right or right to left.
  }
}
    vertical{
  definition {
  Indicating that the address will be rendered from top to bottom or bottom to top.
  }
}
  }
  class DisplayTemplate {
    definition {
  The display template is used for displaying an
interchange address instance belonging to an interchange
address class. Generally, one address class is represented
by one display template.

}
  }
  association {
    owner DisplayTemplate
    member_type inheritance
    member LayoutTemplate
  }
  association {
    owner_type composition
    owner DisplayTemplate
    member_type direct
    member DisplayLine#formLine [1..*]
  }
  class FormTemplate {
    definition {
  This section shows how an input form can be rendered according to
the interchange address class.

The form template should use should also provide an example for display
purposes in input (e.g., Help section).

The form template is used for displaying an input form for entry of address data into an
interchange address instance.
Generally, one address class is represented by one input template.

NOTE: This part has no equivalence in PATDL.

}
  }
  association {
    owner FormTemplate
    member_type inheritance
    member LayoutTemplate
  }
  association {
    owner_type composition
    owner FormTemplate
    member_type direct
    member FormLine#formLine [1..*]
  }
}

Figure 11diagram LayoutLine {
  title 'Layout line'
  caption 'Layout line data model'
  class LayoutLine {
    definition {
  A layout line represents a line in a rendered address display
or an address input form.

It forms the basis of the address display line and
address form line.

}
    +dimensions: LayoutDimension {
  definition {
  Physical dimensions of the rectangular bounding box for the rendered Line.
  }
}
  }
  association {
    owner_type inheritance
    owner LayoutLine
    member_type direct
    member DisplayLine
  }
  association {
    owner_type inheritance
    owner LayoutLine
    member_type direct
    member FormLine
  }
}

Figure 12diagram DisplayTemplate {
  title 'Display template'
  caption 'Display template data model'
  association {
    owner TextElement
    member_type direct
    member DisplayLine
  }
  class DisplayTemplate {
    definition {
  The display template is used for displaying an
interchange address instance belonging to an interchange
address class. Generally, one address class is represented
by one display template.

}
  }
  association {
    owner DisplayTemplate
    member_type inheritance
    member LayoutTemplate
  }
  association {
    owner_type composition
    owner DisplayTemplate
    member_type direct
    member DisplayLine#formLine [1..*]
  }
  class DisplayLine {
    definition {
  A display line represents a line within a display layout.

}
  }
  association {
    owner_type composition
    owner DisplayLine
    member_type direct
    member DisplayLineElement#element [1..*]
  }
  class DisplayLineElement {
    definition {
  This represents an element within a display line.

}
  }
  class DataElement {
    definition {
  Representing a variable data value that is contained in the interchange address component, such as the PO box number following the phrase "PO Box".

}
    +value: CharacterString {
  definition {
  Representing a variable data value that is contained in the interchange address component, such as the PO box number following the phrase "PO Box". This element indicates that a form field is required, and the data values accepted shall adhere to the data value type defined in its associated interchange address component (through `FormLine`).
  }
}
  }
  association {
    owner DataElement
    member_type inheritance
    member DisplayLineElement
  }
  association {
    owner DataElement
    member_type inheritance
    member FormLineElement
  }
  association {
    owner_type inheritance
    owner DataElement
    member_type direct
    member DataElementWithConditions
  }
  class TextElement {
    definition {
  Representing static text, such as the phrase "PO Box" preceding the actual PO box number, for display layouts for PO boxes.

}
    +text: CharacterString {
  definition {
  The actual value of the TextElement.
  }
}
  }
  association {
    owner TextElement
    member_type inheritance
    member DisplayLineElement
  }
}

Figure 13diagram FormTemplate {
  title 'Form template'
  caption 'Form template data model'
  association {
    owner FormTemplate
    member_type direct
    member FormLineElement
  }
  association {
    owner FormLineElement
    member_type direct
    member StaticTextElement
  }
  association {
    owner DataElement
    member_type direct
    member StaticTextElement
  }
  class FormTemplate {
    definition {
  This section shows how an input form can be rendered according to
the interchange address class.

The form template should use should also provide an example for display
purposes in input (e.g., Help section).

The form template is used for displaying an input form for entry of address data into an
interchange address instance.
Generally, one address class is represented by one input template.

NOTE: This part has no equivalence in PATDL.

}
  }
  association {
    owner FormTemplate
    member_type inheritance
    member LayoutTemplate
  }
  association {
    owner_type composition
    owner FormTemplate
    member_type direct
    member FormLine#formLine [1..*]
  }
  class FormLine {
    definition {
  A form line represents a line within a form layout.

It extends from the `LineElementReference` model, and
takes a set of elements that contain
form line element references (`FormLineElementReference`).

}
  }
  association {
    owner_type composition
    owner FormLine
    member_type direct
    member FormLineElement#element [1..*]
  }
  class FormLineElement {
    definition {
  This represents an element within a form line.

In an empty form with fields generated from data elements,
if the `example` values of the associated interchange address component are specified,
such values should be used as placeholders for form input.

}
  }
  class SelectionPair {
    definition {
  Representing a key value pair of a selection, e.g. in the case of the US
States, "Rhode Island" is represented as the displayAs attribute and the
postal code "RI" is represented as the key attribute.

}
    +key: CharacterString {
  definition {
  The mapping key as a unique identifier of the key value pair of this SelectionPair.
  }
}
    +displayAs: CharacterString {
  definition {
  The display value of the key value pair of this SelectionPair.
  }
}
  }
  class SelectionElement {
    definition {
  Representing a selectable mapping between display string to code, e.g. in the case of the US States, "Rhode Island" the state name is mapped to the "RI" postal code. Represented by `SelectionElement` and within `SelectionPair`.
}
    +map: SelectionPair [1..*]{
  definition {
  Mapping between a display string to code for each instance of SelectionPair.
  }
}
  }
  association {
    owner SelectionElement
    member_type inheritance
    member FormLineElement
  }
  class DataElement {
    definition {
  Representing a variable data value that is contained in the interchange address component, such as the PO box number following the phrase "PO Box".

}
    +value: CharacterString {
  definition {
  Representing a variable data value that is contained in the interchange address component, such as the PO box number following the phrase "PO Box". This element indicates that a form field is required, and the data values accepted shall adhere to the data value type defined in its associated interchange address component (through `FormLine`).
  }
}
  }
  association {
    owner DataElement
    member_type inheritance
    member DisplayLineElement
  }
  association {
    owner DataElement
    member_type inheritance
    member FormLineElement
  }
  association {
    owner_type inheritance
    owner DataElement
    member_type direct
    member DataElementWithConditions
  }
  class StaticTextElement {
    definition {
  Static text that can be a constituent part of an `ProfileCompliantAddress` that complies with an `InterchangeAddressClassProfile`.
}
    +value: CharacterString {
  definition {
  Representing static text, such as the phrase "`PO Box`" preceding the actual PO box number, for form layouts for PO boxes. This element is meant to be shown in the form but not allow modification.
  }
}
  }
  association {
    owner StaticTextElement
    member_type inheritance
    member FormLineElement
  }
  class DataElementWithConditions {
    definition {
  DataElementWithConditions extends from DataElement to represent DataElement with additional constraints.
}
    +value: iso19115MD_Constraints {
  definition {
  The constraint information of `MD_Constraint` as defined in <<ISO19115-1>>.
  }
}
  }
}

